MechaDream

A Stable Diffusion model for Mecha

This is a all in one checkpoint (base model + lora + vae) for convenient use.

Please refer to https://civitai.com/models/47025 for the Lora release

Recommended Setting

Sampler: UniPC (Personal preference)

CFG Scale: 15

Negative Embeddings: EasyNegative, bad-hands-5

Lora Weight: 0.8

Hires.fix with scale >= 2 is highly recommend

My workflow

Step 1: Batch generate images

Step 2: Select the best image and inpaint any flaws

Step 3: Upscale using MultiDiffusion

🡳 Some comparison images between original image and after the above workflow 🡳

https://imgsli.com/MTcyNDM2

https://imgsli.com/MTcyNDM3

https://imgsli.com/MTcyNDM5

Roadmap

MechaDream v1 will be the base model for generic mecha image generation

New Lora models train on different anime Blu-ray will add flavors into my MechaDream

Kizuki - Checkpoint Mix

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Attention! First Mayor Update:

First of all, thanks for all the downloads and likes.

The goal of this v2 update was:

  • Improving the age issue

  • Improving eye clarity

  • Improving backgrounds

  • Not breaking too much

If you are switching from V1 to V2 and want to try your old images with the new checkpoint:

Please try out using: Extra -> Variation seed: -1 -> Variation strength: 0,1–0,2

Under normal circumstances, a variation of your old image should be possible to recreate.

Feedback is always appreciated. New Discord thingy here.. still don't really know how it really works, but if your interested or need help:

https://discord.gg/QyHkX7qKtf

Further infos down below!

Kizuki Mix

Within the last few weeks, I really enjoyed discovering stable diffusion, and because of this community, I really got great results out of it.

But as someone who likes to tinker around and personalize things, I wanted to try creating my own mixes and loras.

And because this great community has given me so much, I wanted to give something back.

Depending on the overall feedback and interest, I will update and upload further mixes and loras in the future.

Keep in mind, this mix is made with NSFW related content in mind!

Prompts to get started

Prompt: best quality, masterpiece

Negative: (worst quality: 1.4), (low quality: 1.4),

* Adjust the strength and prompts to your liking, but keep in mind that the negative prompts are very important!

** Use (nsfw:value) positive/negative prompt as needed.

*** Consider adding age tags like: mature female, teen etc.

Settings to use

Most samplers work pretty well, so try out what works for you and pick your favorite.

I'm personally a huge fan of DDIM because it's very fast and I can test prompts and seeds very quickly and make adjustments without much delay.

My "personal" basic settings:

Sampler: DDIM

Steps: 30

Clipskip: 2

CFG Scale: 10

VAE: Included in Checkpoint

HiRes fix: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

HiRes Steps: 25

HiRes Denoise: 25

Upscale by 1x for prompt or seed testing and higher for final results.

Embeddings:

Sometimes they can help your results a lot, but they can also screw you over. So try adding or removing them from your prompts for different results.

Easy Negative

bad prompt

bad hands

bad artist

Loras:

Most of them should work out pretty well, but I would suggest to start with low values like 0.1/0.2 start increasing until you get the result you want.

Special thanks:

Unfortunately, I did not keep track of every resource author I used when I first started mixing and testing... Therefore, credit and huge thanks to all Civitai creators!

Last but no least:

If you like my mix it would mean a lot to me if you leave a like, support me with a ko-fi or share your results / prompts with this great community!

Fleeting-Radiance Mix

Fleeting-Radiance Mix

在刹那间绽放的光彩，如同人生中一瞬的璀璨，飞逝而过，却又在心灵深处留下永不磨灭的印记

The fleeting radiance, like a momentary brilliance in the fleetingness of life, passes by in a flash, yet leaves an indelible impression deep in the soul

Introduction：

Chinese:

一个泛用的，比较清爽的二次元模型（自认为）

在融合过程中，我追求细节，结构与稳定

不过，请注意，FR在融合过程中，从未、以后也不会使用到2.5D和真人模型，

这是一个纯粹的二次元模型

我推荐使用最新版本的FRMiX，因为在迭代过程中，我尽力让新版本表现得比先前更好

不过，如果你喜欢先前某一版本的画风，也可以下载对应版本

在设置上，我推荐高分辨率，竖图（如600*960），高清修复（算法我常用4x-UltraSharp和R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B，重绘幅度0.3-0.4）

采样器我推荐 DPM++ SDE Karras，步数30-60（我常用60，细节更到位）

提示词相关性5-7

vae我使用的是clearvae，不过我并没有将它整合入模型，你可以选用你喜欢的vae

如果你需要fp16版本，请告知我（否则我仅会在最终版发布时同时发布一个最终版的fp16版本）

希望大家能够反馈自己生成的图片，这可以帮助我改进FR，谢谢大家！

我的bilibili（欢迎私信）：

https://space.bilibili.com/351739534

English:

My English level is very poor, so I had GPT translate this for me:

A general, relatively refreshing 2D model (at least I think so).

During the fusion process, I pursue details, structure, and stability.

However, please note that FR has never and will never use 2.5D or human models in the fusion process.

This is a purely 2D model.

I recommend using the latest version of FRMiX, because I have tried to make the new version perform better than the previous one during the iteration process.

However, if you like the style of a previous version, you can download the corresponding version.

For settings, I recommend high resolution, portrait orientation (such as 600*960), and high-definition repair (I often use the algorithms 4x-UltraSharp and R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, with a Denoising of 0.3-0.4).

I recommend using the DPM++ SDE Karras sampler, with 30-60 steps (I often use 60 for more accurate details).

The CFG Scale should be 5-7.

I use clearvae for VAE, but I haven't integrated it into the model. You can use your favorite VAE.

If you need an fp16 version, please let me know (otherwise, I will only release an fp16 version with the final version).

I hope everyone can provide feedback on the images they generate, as this can help me improve FR. Thank you!

MoonMix

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

2023.4.21

我将胶片风Lora小比例融合进了Fantasy模型中，优化了此模型下皮肤的质感。但请注意，要获得完美的胶片质感，仍需要搭配胶片风Lora使用，只是使用比例可以降低0.1~0.15左右。

Fantasy 2.0模型更偏幻想风格一些，Reality 2.0模型更偏写实风格一些。两个模型质量都不错，大家可以根据需求下载使用。

2023.4.20

更新了reality2.0版本，这个版本相比之前两个版本，较大幅度提升了皮肤和样貌的真实感。建议在生成人像时，搭配胶片感Lora（1girlmix）使用，真实感更佳。

同时最重要的，新模型搭配兔狲Lora使用，生成兔狲逼真图像的成功率大幅提升！（没错，我搞这个模型，其实主要是为了训练猫猫）

chilloutmix模型与本模型的reality版本、fantasy版本的对比：

Comparison between the chilloutmix model and the reality and fantasy versions of this model:

我比较推荐用reality版本的模型，在色调、颜值和真实性上比较平衡。建议将clip skip设为1，这样生成的图会更美观。

I recommend using the reality version of the model, which is more balanced in tone, appearance and authenticity.

本模型由多个checkpoint模型合并而来，具体有哪些我也记不太清了。以下是MoonMix与chilloutMix模型在生成人像时的一些对比。总的来说，MoonMix相比chilloutMix，真实感和锐度有所下降，但美感与丰富度有所提升。

This model is the result of merging several checkpoint models. I can't remember exactly which models there are. Here are some comparisons between MoonMix and chilloutMix models in generating portraits. In general, MoonMix is less realistic and sharper than chilloutMix, but the overall beauty and richness is improved.

DREAD V4

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

LORA-V4 VERSION HERE

A custom build model using SD1.5 as a base. Trained on 30k images ove it's 4 versions, of horror and psychological terror, with a very graining and dark aesthetic. The images were hand sorted to make sure they fit the style and theme I was looking for, and after auto-tagging were then manually tagged with more clear identifiers and themes to help push generation even further.

If you are looking for crisp and clean images, go elsewhere. This is one grainy boi.


V4 now out!

Dread V4 adds upon 2 and 3(not posted) with 20k images, custom sorted and tagged, before training. It adds a greater variety of horror based subject matter, and more keywords specifically trained into it's data.

USE TIPS

Certain keywords work well invoking feelings and moods in pictures generated with this model. Here are some of the tags used specifically in training data tagging to keep some effects consistent.
Try using any the following in your prompts:

  • found footage, disposable camera, trailcam: For that grainy look with washed-out colours and faded edges.

  • liminal, abandoned, hallway, house, forest, swamp: Indoor and outdoor locations that are empty, earie, and even a bit run down.

  • body horror, visceral, circulatory system, viscera, organs, blood, injury: Various words indicating different types of mutations or styles.

  • dendrophobia, plants, mushroom, fungus, vines, roots: Vines overtaking objects, creatures made of roots, mushrooms growing out of the skin. Anything plant related.

  • diagram, illustration: Medical and botany illustration like style, redacted documents, sketches

  • tome, grimoire, arcane, sigil, magic symbol: Unholy and eerie works or writings to behold

  • experiment, medical, research, lab, malpractice: Creepy labs, glass tubes, shady science, deranged doctors offices- these tags help with those sorts of settings.

  • entity, creature, being, monster, animal: Tags used for various oddities and scary things that go bump in the night.

  • trypophobia, holes: Lots of holes, lots of growths, lots of repeating circular shapes across things.

  • torture, suffering, pain: The screams of the damned at your command

  • religious, demonic, ritual, cult: circles of people gathered by candle light, alters and holy (unholy?) figures abound

  • and many more...

Push the style further

Use DREAD in your prompt, all caps, to reinforce the horror aesthetic. Only the best images were tagged with this, and it can change your generations greatly. This is not a required tag, however! All images for training contained the word 'horror' in their tags.

Lora extraction in the works, will be listed separate from this model, unlike last time.

Today, I'm presenting to you "Juggernaut," a side project that emerged during my work. In the past, I was always annoyed when I had to switch models to achieve different styles, so I had been working on another model (StaVis) for some time. Juggernaut is an extremely versatile model that can serve several style directions (paintings, digital, realism, anime, NSFW) and delivers absolutely sharp quality. The sample images are the raw output from Stable Diffusion. The standard VAE was used, so you can experiment with your own VAEs.

Falkons (Anime and Hentai)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Preface: trigger words and ready-to-go example

This model has no trigger words, but I highly suggest to use negative prompt, which let you refine your creations, I am going to leave an example.

Example:

Prompt: a girl,
Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark,
Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 2118282899, Size: 640x960, Model hash: 460b71c1c2, Model: Falkons

Introduction

In the world of anime, style and aesthetics play a huge role in creating memorable and captivating characters. From bold and vibrant colors to intricate and detailed designs, there's no limit to the creativity that can be expressed through anime. In this model, we embrace the anime style and bring it to life with our own unique spin. Each character is carefully crafted to embody the essence of the anime universe, with exaggerated features and dynamic poses that capture the imagination. So if you're looking for a model that truly captures the spirit of anime, look no further than our collection.

How to install

  1. Download and install Stable Diffusion, I personally suggest the executable version by AUTOMATIC1111.

  2. Download Falkons model in .safetensor format and insert it into the "ckpt" folder.

  3. Start Stable Diffusion.

  4. Select the "Falkons.safetensor" model from the "Stable Diffusion checkpoint" dropdown menu.

Install add-ons and plug-ins: LORA, Textual Inversion, Extensions

This model is compatible with LORAs, Textual Inversion embeddings and Stable Diffusion's extensions, just download your favourites and put them rispectively in stable-diffusion-webui/models/Lora, stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings and stable-diffusion-webui/extensions.

Each add-on has its own trigger words or tags to be added in prompt in order to be triggered. In Stable Diffusion Web UI, you can click on the "show/hide extra networks" button, right below the Generate button, here you can click on Refresh, then on Textual Inversion tab or Lora tab, finally you can click on your wanted add-on to automatically add the trigger words or tags.

I highly suggest EasyNegative and bad-hands-5, download EasyNegative.safetensor and bad-hands-5.pt from https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative and https://huggingface.co/yesyeahvh/bad-hands-5/, copy them in stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings, and use the words EasyNegative, bad-hands-5 as negative prompt to trigger them.

How to use

Of course you can try it with the prompt, sampling methods, steps, CFG, etc. you desire, I use to generate images with:

  • Sampling methods: Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras or DDIM

    • Euler a for a more toon effect

    • DPM++ SDE Karras for an higher realistic effect

    • DDIM for faster generation and still good quality, I renew you the suggestion to use EasyNegative embedding (read the paragraph above)

  • Sampling steps: I usually set a minimum of 20 steps, more steps often help to generate a more detailed image, but it's not always true, and typically there is less difference as the number of steps increases

  • Restore faces, Tiling and Hires. fix turned off

  • Dimensions: I suggest you to choose multiple of 64. I usually pick 640x960, but I have noticed good results with other resolutions such as 512x512, 512x704, 512x960, 624x1176, 720x1024, 960x1280, while I have experienced poor results with bigger resolutions you can still generate low-resolution images first, then use stable diffusion img2img to increase their resolution through upscaling techniques, e.g. you can generate a 640x960 picture and then upscale it to 1280x1920, increasing both quality and details; I will update this readme with more details later

  • Batch size and batch count: my GPU can handle a Batch size of 5, which means 5 images generated per run at once, it really depends on your GPU's VRAM, so find the highest number of batch size you can handle. With batch count, Stable Diffusion starts a new run automatically after the previous one, so you get the multiplication result of the two numbers (e.g. batch size: 5, and batch count: 10, means 50 output images)

Examples

Example 1

You can start with very easy prompt, such as:

Prompt: a girl,
Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark,
Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 2118282899, Size: 640x960, Model hash: 460b71c1c2, Model: Falkons

XenoEngine Art Style

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

I wanted a model or workflow process that allowed me to quickly and easily churn out art for games and/or photo stories. I didn't want long complicated prompts to create a certain art style, but I also didn't want to be forced to use LoRa's and TI's for every character. Unfortunately, most of the models where I loved the art styles didn't do so well of loading characters (celebrities for mixing, fictional characters, etc.) and the ones that knew tons of famous characters and people tended not take to the art styles I was going for (at least not without complex prompts).

There are some great Anime style art prompts that did a nice job, but I didn't really want Anime faces (big eyes, heart shaped head with pointy chin, etc.). A wanted more of a western style, with a hint of caricature in the faces, and a consistent look from a basic <character> is wearing <outfit> at <location> type prompt.

Unfortunately, since I didn't really expect this to work, I didn't start taking notes on what all went into this until I was fairly well along. It started with a Mega Model (either SD's AIO or Clarity - I forget) and then I merged Rev Animated and Babes into that.

To my surprise, it knew LOTS of characters and celebrities (even some obscure ones that I was surprised about) and it spit out a pretty consistent style - even though it was still a bit more realistic than I wanted. It took LoRa's and style tokens well, though... so I moved to the next phase.

First I added several LoRa styles that I liked the looks of and tweaked the weights on each. They were styles that needed no triggers - so hopefully once I merged them in, then my default prompt would spit out that style every time. (Fingers crossed). I set the values so they showed up, but were low enough that the style didn't affect the clothes or other compositional elements much (if at all). The styles and the weights I ended up at are as follows: <LuisapNijijourneyLORAV2_v2:0.7>,<bootyFarmStyleLora_v10Dim128:0.4>, <lora:hungryClickerStyle_v20:0.6>

To my shock and amazement - it worked spectacularly. It wasn't quite the style I wanted, but adding simply: (bold lines:1.1), (high color), ((smooth skin)), (Masterpiece Digital Artwork:1.3), to the start of the prompt got me there. I can handle a 4 token seed prompt.

Some notes on the model:

  • It "mostly" defaults to SFW out of the box. i.e. If you just type in a person's name or character description with no clothes - it'll tend to put them in clothes - or at least a swimsuit. That said... with proper prompting, does nudes and porny stuff just fine, too.

  • I didn't care so much about making sure resulting characters look "exactly" like the person you're calling out so much as wanting to make sure that if I called out that name/person again - they'd be consistent in the way they look from image to image. So, in other words, it's not so much about "accuracy" as it is about "consistency" - and that seems to come through. (This works well for my needs to create stories and whatnot)

  • Depending upon the distance from camera (i.e. Closeup head shots vs. full body shots) the weight of the "bold lines" in (many of) my example prompts can be tweaked. The further back, the lower that should go and the closer in, the higher it can go.

  • This model (probably due to one of the LoRa styles I added) tends to want to add tattoos - even for those characters who don't have them. Adding that to the negative prompt can help (see below). Don't forget to remove those if you actually want the tattoos there.

  • I've added some comments to several of the example images - especially the ones without generation data.

For the sample images I used the Anything VAE (though it works fine with both the default and Anime VAEs that I tried with it). No textual inversions or LoRa usage in them - it's all coming from the checkpoint. Base images at 384x512, Euler a at 20 steps, clip skip 2, face restoration, and scale fix (2x size using latent bicubic/antialiased). The first few examples are pure raw with just a character name and/or character name + general outfit description.

Those first few examples have no negative prompt, either (just to show how well it generally behaves without them). A good neg prompt helps with various things like extra fingers/bad hands, various defects and so on. The one I use most often is: (snagged from a sample image somewhere at some point)


canvas frame, 3d, ((disfigured)), ((bad art)), ((deformed)),((extra limbs)),((b&w)), blurry, (((duplicate))), ((morbid)), ((mutilated)), [out of frame], extra fingers, mutated hands, ((poorly drawn hands)), ((poorly drawn face)), (((mutation))), (((deformed))), ((ugly)), blurry, ((bad anatomy)), (((bad proportions))), ((extra limbs)), cloned face, (((disfigured))), out of frame, ugly, extra limbs, (bad anatomy), gross proportions, (malformed limbs), ((missing arms)), ((missing legs)), (((extra arms))), (((extra legs))), mutated hands, (fused fingers), (too many fingers), (((long neck))), ugly, tiling, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn feet, poorly drawn face, out of frame, mutation, mutated, extra limbs, extra legs, extra arms, disfigured, deformed, cross-eye, body out of frame, blurry, bad art, bad anatomy, Scribbles, Low quality, Low rated, Mediocre, 3D rendering, Screenshot, Software, UI, watermark, signature, distorted pupils, distorted eyes, (distorted face), Unnatural anatomy, strange anatomy, things on face, ((tattoo)), ((tattoos)),

Obviously, some of those may want to be removed if you're going for something that has been excluded.
